<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="251" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="24.[813,1456,473,603]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">
<typeStatus box="[813,861,474,497]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">TYPE</typeStatus>
LOCALITY. — Not mentioned in the original description, but “Galliae” according to title of Catalogus. From 
<bibRefCitation author="DUPUY D." box="[1265,1455,499,524]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251" refId="ref25398" refString="DUPUY D. 1851. - Histoire naturelle des mollusques terrestres et d'eau douce qui vivent en France, Masson, Paris &amp; Brun, Auch (Fascicule 5): Tit. + p. 459 - 594, pls 22 - 24. Available online at: http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org" type="url" year="1851">Dupuy (1851: 553)</bibRefCitation>
the following 
<typeStatus box="[949,991,526,550]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">type</typeStatus>
locality can be reconstructed: “Habit. Les eaux tranquilles de la 
<collectingCountry box="[979,1044,553,576]" name="France" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">France</collectingCountry>
méditerranéenne, les environs de Grasse, marais de la Népoule (Mouton), etc.”
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[813,1456,636,713]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="MNHN-, MNHN-JOU" pageId="24" pageNumber="251" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="syntype">
TYPES. — 
<typeStatus box="[920,1007,636,660]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">Syntypes</typeStatus>
unknown. For topotypes compare 
<figureCitation box="[1364,1455,636,660]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="21.[131,142,1871,1889]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[132,1455,215,1840]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIG. 11. — A-C, Mercuria meridionalis (Risso, 1826), France, Var, Foux de Draguignan, leg. Boeters 27.IX.1969, BOE 2414 ex 0261 (A, B); BOE 2151 ex 0261 (C); A, ♀; B, ♂; C, ♂, pallial tentacle, copulatory organ and pedal lobe clearly to be seen; D, E, Mercuria sp., presumable topotypes of Bithinia [sic] moutonii Dupuy, 1849; D, France, Alpes-Maritimes, Cannes (i.e. Mandelieu-la-Napoule [Népoule sensu Dupuy]), ♀ (MNHN-LOC); E, France, Var, Grasse (MNHN-JOU); F, Mercuria corsensis n. sp. France, Corse-du-Sud, Bonifacio, Couvent de la Trinité, leg Boeters IX.1979 (holotype MNHN-IM-2000-31951 ex BOE 0916); G-H, Mercuria zopissa (Paulucci, 1882), Italy, Sardinia, Monte dei Sette Fratelli, leg Giusti, Topotypes ex SMF 252038/7; G, globular shell; H, slender shell; I-J, Pseudamnicola emiliana (Paladilhe 1869); I, Neotype ex Topotype; France, Hérault, ruisseau [d’eaux douces] près de Balaruc (MNHN-IM-2000-32541 ex de Folin); J, de Folin’s label [“determ. par Paladilhe”, handwriting de Folin]. Scale bars: A, B, D-I, 3 mm; C, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5154189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5154189/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
(“Cannes” corresponds to Siagne at Mandelieu-la-Napoule; 
<collectionCode box="[1367,1456,663,686]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">MNHN-</collectionCode>
LOC) and 
<figureCitation box="[921,1004,688,713]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="21.[131,142,1871,1889]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[132,1455,215,1840]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIG. 11. — A-C, Mercuria meridionalis (Risso, 1826), France, Var, Foux de Draguignan, leg. Boeters 27.IX.1969, BOE 2414 ex 0261 (A, B); BOE 2151 ex 0261 (C); A, ♀; B, ♂; C, ♂, pallial tentacle, copulatory organ and pedal lobe clearly to be seen; D, E, Mercuria sp., presumable topotypes of Bithinia [sic] moutonii Dupuy, 1849; D, France, Alpes-Maritimes, Cannes (i.e. Mandelieu-la-Napoule [Népoule sensu Dupuy]), ♀ (MNHN-LOC); E, France, Var, Grasse (MNHN-JOU); F, Mercuria corsensis n. sp. France, Corse-du-Sud, Bonifacio, Couvent de la Trinité, leg Boeters IX.1979 (holotype MNHN-IM-2000-31951 ex BOE 0916); G-H, Mercuria zopissa (Paulucci, 1882), Italy, Sardinia, Monte dei Sette Fratelli, leg Giusti, Topotypes ex SMF 252038/7; G, globular shell; H, slender shell; I-J, Pseudamnicola emiliana (Paladilhe 1869); I, Neotype ex Topotype; France, Hérault, ruisseau [d’eaux douces] près de Balaruc (MNHN-IM-2000-32541 ex de Folin); J, de Folin’s label [“determ. par Paladilhe”, handwriting de Folin]. Scale bars: A, B, D-I, 3 mm; C, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5154189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5154189/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">Fig. 11E</figureCitation>
(Var, Grasse; 
<collectionCode box="[1140,1283,689,713]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">MNHN-JOU</collectionCode>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="251" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[811,1457,758,1613]" box="[813,913,758,784]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[811,1457,758,1613]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">
It would be of interest to clarify whether the ecological indication “les eaux tranquilles” might differentiate Dupuy’s species from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Risso" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[871,1037,853,879]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Mercuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="24" pageNumber="251" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis box="[871,1037,853,879]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">M. meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[811,1457,758,1613]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">
A sample in the Collection Dupuy (MHNT-DUP) (
<bibRefCitation author="ASTRE G." pageId="24" pageNumber="251" pagination="251 - 263" refId="ref23874" refString="ASTRE G. 1921. - Recherches sur les Mollusques terrestres et d'eau douce, VII. La serie de types conchyliologiques etablie par l'abbe Dupuy pour le Museum de Toulouse. Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire naturelle de Toulouse 49 (3): 251 - 263. Available online at: http: // gallica. bnf. fr" type="journal article" year="1921">Astre 1921: 262</bibRefCitation>
) from Draguignan is not regarded as 
<typeStatus box="[1355,1451,917,943]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">syntypes</typeStatus>
, since it does not come from the reconstructed type locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[811,1457,758,1613]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">
Grasse was the domicile of the collector Mouton and the “marais de la Népoule” is surely identical with the historical Étang de la Napoule which is described by 
<bibRefCitation author="DESMAREST N." pageId="24" pageNumber="251" pagination="98" refId="ref25175" refString="DESMAREST N. 1811. - Article &quot; Etang de la Napoule. &quot; In Encyclopedie methodique, ou par ordre de matieres. Geographie-physique. H. Agasse, Paris, 4: 98. Available on-line at: http: // books. google. com" type="journal article" year="1811">Desmarest (1811: 98)</bibRefCitation>
as “ancien lit” of the lower course of the river Siagne and as a pestilential swamp consisting of “une infinité de petites mares”. The spelling variant “Népoule” instead of “Napoule” is at least documented by the geologist 
<bibRefCitation author="COQUAND H." pageId="24" pageNumber="251" refId="ref24739" refString="COQUAND H. 1836. - Notice mineralogique de l'Esterel, et en general du departement du Var. Bulletin de la Societe geologique de France, 7 [1835 / 1836]: 107 - 116. Available online at: http: // jubilotheque. upmc. fr / ead. html? id = GB _ 000007 _ 001" type="url" year="1836">Coquand (1836: 111)</bibRefCitation>
. In this context it should finally be mentioned that the Collection Pascal (MNHN-PAS) comprises a sample of 
<taxonomicName box="[841,938,1268,1293]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Mercuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="24" pageNumber="251" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[841,938,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">Mercuria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Mandelieu[-la-Napoule] (MNHN-PAS/3 ex de Folin [5]).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[811,1457,758,1613]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">
<materialsCitation collectorName="A. Mace" location="Cannes" pageId="24" pageNumber="251" specimenCount="1">
A large sample has been collected before 1875 by 
<collectorName box="[1365,1455,1331,1358]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">A. Macé</collectorName>
in the Siagne near its embouchure between 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:CF74879AE604FF9DFC5AAE5A8033B0D6:42026057E604FF9DFAEEAA3F803EB316" box="[1291,1371,1363,1389]" name="Cannes" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">Cannes</location>
and La Napoule
</materialsCitation>
; 
<materialsCitation collectionCode="MNHN-LOC" county="Locard" location="Mousson" municipality="As" pageId="24" pageNumber="251" specimenCode="ZMH 524050" specimenCount="149">
from this material a large lot of 
<specimenCount box="[1253,1411,1395,1421]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251" type="generic">149 specimens</specimenCount>
was donated to 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:CF74879AE604FF9DFC5AAE5A8033B0D6:42026057E604FF9DFC49AAF88175B3D5" box="[940,1040,1428,1454]" county="Locard" municipality="As" name="Mousson" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">Mousson</location>
(
<specimenCode box="[1056,1217,1427,1454]" collectionCode="ZMH" country="Germany" name="Zoologisches Museum Hamburg" pageId="24" pageNumber="251" type="Museum">ZMH 524050</specimenCode>
and 524051). 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1385,1412,1427,1453]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">As</collectingMunicipality>
the shells with indication of locality “Cannes” in the collection 
<collectingCounty box="[814,888,1491,1517]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">Locard</collectingCounty>
(
<collectionCode box="[900,1059,1491,1517]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">MNHN-LOC</collectionCode>
) show an identical mud coating it can be presumed that they stem from the same sampling
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[811,1457,758,1613]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">
There do not exist any recent reports of 
<taxonomicName box="[1293,1392,1555,1580]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Mercuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="24" pageNumber="251" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1293,1392,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">Mercuria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Grasse and its environs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[902,1366,1682,1772]" box="[902,1366,1682,1709]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boeters &amp; Falkner" authorityYear="2017" box="[902,1366,1682,1709]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Pseudamnicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="24" pageNumber="251" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="emilianus" status="n. comb." subGenus="Pseudamnicola">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[902,1366,1682,1709]" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[902,1065,1682,1709]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">Pseudamnicola</emphasis>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1081,1244,1682,1709]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">Pseudamnicola</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1260,1366,1682,1709]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="251">emilianus</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
